While Sieve_of_Eratosthenes is good for finding all prime upto a power, it is not good for finding whether a given number is prime. In this case modulas method is good. But the algorithm of first answer is inefficien( because it checks upto x-1 while checking upto square root of x is sufficient).
A better algorithm is

int isPrime(x){
for(i=0;i<(int)sqrt(x);i++)
if(x%i)==0 return 0;

return 1;
}

